.TH "pci_epf_test_data_transfer" 9 "pci_epf_test_data_transfer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_epf_test_data_transfer \- Function that uses dmaengine API to transfer data between PCIe EP and remote PCIe RC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_epf_test_data_transfer
.BI "(struct pci_epf_test *epf_test "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t dma_dst "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t dma_src "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "epf_test" 12
the EPF test device that performs the data transfer operation
.IP "dma_dst" 12
The destination address of the data transfer. It can be a physical
address given by pci_epc_mem_alloc_addr or DMA mapping APIs.
.IP "dma_src" 12
The source address of the data transfer. It can be a physical
address given by pci_epc_mem_alloc_addr or DMA mapping APIs.
.IP "len" 12
The size of the data transfer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Function that uses dmaengine API to transfer data between PCIe EP and remote
PCIe RC. The source and destination address can be a physical address given
by pci_epc_mem_alloc_addr or the one obtained using DMA mapping APIs.

The function returns '0' on success and negative value on failure.
